.TH "__rt_mutex_init" 9 "__rt_mutex_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__rt_mutex_init \- initialize the rt_mutex
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __rt_mutex_init
.BI "(struct rt_mutex *lock "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct lock_class_key *key "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lock" 12
The rt_mutex to be initialized
.IP "name" 12
The lock name used for debugging
.IP "key" 12
The lock class key used for debugging
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialize the rt_mutex to unlocked state.

Initializing of a locked rt_mutex is not allowed
